Sentencas: Cation ordered perovskites have been recognized as advanced cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Optimization of Sr content in layered SmBa1-xSrxCo2O5+δ perovskite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This study focuses on the effects of Sr substitution on crystal characteristics, electrical properties, and electrochemical performance of SmBa1-xSrxCo2O5+delta (x = 0, 0.25, 0.5, 0.75, and 1.0) as an IT-SOFC cathode material.
Titulo: Optimization of Sr content in layered SmBa1-xSrxCo2O5+δ perovskite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity improves with increasing Sr content due to the greater amount of electronic holes originated from the increased interstitial oxygen.
Titulo: Optimization of Sr content in layered SmBa1-xSrxCo2O5+δ perovskite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The area specific resistances (ASRs) of SmBa1-xSrxCo2O5, decrease with Sr content up to x = 0.75 and increase abruptly for x = 1.
Titulo: Optimization of Sr content in layered SmBa1-xSrxCo2O5+δ perovskite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: For x = 0.75, the lowest ASR value, 0.138 Omega cm(2), and the highest single cell performance, 1.039 W cm(-2) at 600 degrees C, are obtained.
Titulo: Optimization of Sr content in layered SmBa1-xSrxCo2O5+δ perovskite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: These results indicate that SmBa1-xSrxCo2O5+delta is optimized at x = 0.75 in terms of obtaining the best performance for IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Optimization of Sr content in layered SmBa1-xSrxCo2O5+δ perovskite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
